{"id":"6788","name":"Sort List Numerically [JS1]","tagline":"A JavaScript one-liner to sort a list of numbers","icon":"ios12 c255 g59445","latest":"21445","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<p><strong>NOTE:</strong> <a href=\"https://www.reddit.com/r/shortcuts/comments/qsafoh/filter_files_now_sort_numerically/\">Somewhere between iOS 14.8.1 and iOS 15.2 the \"Filter Files\" action started sorting numerically</a>, making this snippet obsolete except for backwards compatibility, or as an example of the custom sorting capabilities of embedding JavaScript in a Shortcut.</p>\n<p>A single line of JavaScript that takes a list of numbers and sorts them numerically. The list can come from a “Create list” action, or from text (one list item per line). List operations are surprisingly limited in Shortcuts. This snippet and others like it <a href=\"https://routinehub.co/shortcut/6787/\">[1]</a><a href=\"https://routinehub.co/shortcut/7016/\">[2]</a><a href=\"https://routinehub.co/shortcut/6790/\">[3]</a> try to fill this gap.</p>\n<p>See also <a href=\"https://routinehub.co/user/EggsistentialBread\">@EggsistentialBread</a>'s \"<a href=\"https://routinehub.co/shortcut/8679/\">De-Duplicate List</a>\" and \"<a href=\"https://routinehub.co/shortcut/8707/\">Add at Index</a>\" for additional list operations.</p>\n<p><strong>NOTE:</strong> If the region in use uses a comma as decimal separator, it will need to be replaced by a period for this shortcut to work.</p>\n<h4>Your own sort method</h4>\n<p>The numerical sort of this shortcut is achieved by using a custom sort function:</p>\n<pre><code>(a,b)=&gt;a-b\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Other sortings can be used, but a clear criteria is needed. For example, to sort resolutions like 1280×720 and 1200×800, which of them goes first? If the criteria is <em>\"first width, then height\"</em> 1200×800 would go before 1280×720. But if the criteria is <em>\"amount of pixels\"</em>, 1280×720 (0.922 Mpx) would go before 1200×800 (0.96 Mpx).</p>\n<h4>Don't download the shortcut</h4>\n<p>If you just want the code, there's no need to download the shortcut. Copy this and paste it in a \"URL\" action:</p>\n<pre><code>data:text/html,&lt;script&gt;let list=`REPLACETHISWITHLISTVARIABLE`;document.write(list.split(\"\\n\").sort((a,b)=&gt;a-b).join('&lt;br&gt;'))&lt;/script&gt;\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Replace the <code>REPLACETHISWITHLISTVARIABLE</code> fragment with the variable contaning the list, add a \"Get File of Type\" with type <code>com.apple.webarchive</code> below, and split its output with new lines to get the sorted list.</p>\n<p>I use \"Get File of Type\" instead of \"Get Contents of Webpage\" to avoid that the user is misleading told that the shortcut uses Safari.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>No error checking</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://editor.scpl.dev/?scpl=%40Icon%20list%0A%40Color%20darkgray%0AComment%20%22A%20JavaScript%20one-liner%20to%20sort%20a%20list%20of%20numbers%20%E2%80%94%20%40atnbueno%20%282020-10-03%29%5Cn%5Cn-%20The%20list%20can%20come%20from%20a%20%E2%80%9CCreate%20list%E2%80%9D%20action%2C%20or%20from%20text%20%28one%20list%20item%20per%20line%29%5Cn-%20The%20JavaScript%20output%20must%20be%20split%20into%20lines%20to%20get%20the%20list%20format%20back%22%0AList%20%5B2020%2C%2010%2C%203%2C%209.55%5D%20-%3E%20mv%3AList%0AURL%20%22data%3Atext%2Fhtml%2C%3Cscript%3Elet%20list%3D%60%5C%28mv%3AList%29%60%3Bdocument.write%28list.split%28%5C%22%5C%5Cn%5C%22%29.sort%28%28a%2Cb%29%3D%3Ea-b%29.join%28%27%3Cbr%3E%27%29%29%3C%2Fscript%3E%22%20-%3E%20mv%3AURL%0AGetFileofType%20%22com.apple.webarchive%22%20-%3E%20mv%3A%22Get%20File%20of%20Type%22%0AShowResult%20%22Input%3A%5Cn%5C%28mv%3AList%29%5Cn%5CnOutput%3A%5Cn%5C%28mv%3A%22Get%20File%20of%20Type%22%7Bas%3A%20text%7D%29%22\">ScPL source</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Array/sort\"><code>Array.prototype.sort()</code> documentation at MDN</a></li>\n</ul>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>1.0.0 - Oct. 3, 2020,